{
  "text": "Any increase in antigen or clinical worsening during or after treatment should be investigated by evaluating itraconazole blood concentration, adherence to treatment, CD4 count and HIV viral load. Nonadherence to therapy was the main predictor for relapse of histoplasmosis. [CITATION_1] Clinical worsening during therapy may represent treatment failure, immune reconstitution inflammatory syndrome (IRIS) or a different opportunistic infection.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1049539"
